abstract: Gillian Gill’s new biography, “Virginia Woolf: And the Women Who Shaped Her World,” traces the influences of her female family members and friends on the author’s career.

abstract: Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro on Friday defended his son from accusations of corruption and attacked the Rio de Janeiro state prosecutors leading an investigation of Senator Flavio Bolsonaro's alleged money laundering and misuse of public funds.
snippet: Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro on Friday defended his son from accusations of corruption and attacked the Rio de Janeiro state prosecutors leading an investigation of Senator Flavio Bolsonaro's alleged money laundering and misuse of public fun...
lead_paragraph: RIO DE JANEIRO/BRASILIA — Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro on Friday defended his son from accusations of corruption and attacked the Rio de Janeiro state prosecutors leading an investigation of Senator Flavio Bolsonaro's alleged money laundering and misuse of public funds.
headline_main: Brazil's Bolsonaro Defends Son Against Deepening Graft Probe
headline_print_headline: Brazil's Bolsonaro Defends Son Against Deepening Graft Probe

abstract: An investigation concluded that the Treasury Department’s top spokeswoman did not commit research misconduct, but required extensive revisions.
snippet: An investigation concluded that the Treasury Department’s top spokeswoman did not commit research misconduct, but required extensive revisions.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Monica Crowley, the Treasury Department’s assistant secretary for public affairs, committed “localized instances of plagiarism” in her 2000 Ph.D. dissertation, Columbia University found in an investigation that ultimately concluded she did not commit research misconduct.

abstract: The Democratic National Committee is again upping its polling and fundraising requirements for presidential hopefuls to qualify for participating in the campaign's seventh debate in January, the first in a series of four held in the earliest-voting states.
snippet: The Democratic National Committee is again upping its polling and fundraising requirements for presidential hopefuls to qualify for participating in the campaign's seventh debate in January, the first in a series of four held in the earliest-votin...
lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — The Democratic National Committee is again upping its polling and fundraising requirements for presidential hopefuls to qualify for participating in the campaign's seventh debate in January, the first in a series of four held in the earliest-voting states.
headline_main: Party Again Ups Stakes for 7th Democratic Candidate Debate
headline_print_headline: Party Again Ups Stakes for 7th Democratic Candidate Debate

abstract: Only Joe Biden, Pete Buttigieg, Amy Klobuchar, Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren have met the new criteria to take part in the debate, scheduled for Jan. 14 in Des Moines.
snippet: Only Joe Biden, Pete Buttigieg, Amy Klobuchar, Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren have met the new criteria to take part in the debate, scheduled for Jan. 14 in Des Moines.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — One day after seven candidates took the stage for the most intimate debate of the Democratic presidential primary cycle so far, the Democratic National Committee increased the qualification standards for its next debate in January, making it likely that the field of candidates will be winnowed even further for the event.

lead_paragraph: Sarah Huckabee Sanders apologized late Thursday after she mocked comments by former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. during the Democratic presidential debate in which he recounted mentoring a boy who had a speech impediment.
